The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Under the scanner

 THE JAMAICA PEGASUS 

The hotel: The Jamaica Pegasus is a four-star hotel in the heart of Kingston. The 17-storied hotel is marketed as the preferred address in the Jamaican capital. 

Accommodation: There are 300 air-conditioned rooms, including 16 one-bedroom suites and three luxury suites. There also are special rooms for the physically challenged. 

Restaurants: There are three restaurants and two bars, 

Celebrity guests: The hotel has hosted personalities like Pope John Paul II, Nelson Mandela and Fidel Castro, besides national cricket teams, Presidents and Prime Ministers. (agencies) 




